ContainerSettings.Title: Date
ContainerSettings.Description: Select the date range as last month or custom range to visualize the data.

ContainerSettings.Title: Patients Count by Week
ContainerSettings.Description: Weekly basis patients count (outpatients and inpatients).

ContainerSettings.Title: Doctors
ContainerSettings.Description: It shows the total number of doctors under the organization.

ContainerSettings.Title: Readmission Rate
ContainerSettings.Description: Readmission means patients who are discharged from hospital and again admitted within a specific time period. Readmission rate is calculated by dividing the number of readmission by the total number of admissions.

ContainerSettings.Title: Bed Occupancy Rate
ContainerSettings.Description: Bed Occupancy Rate can be calculated by dividing the number of beds effectively occupied by the number of beds available.

ContainerSettings.Title: Admitted Patients
ContainerSettings.Description: Total of patients admitted in the hospital.

ContainerSettings.Title: Patients
ContainerSettings.Description: It shows the patients count of all ages by gender wise.

ContainerSettings.Title: Average Length of Stay
ContainerSettings.Description:
Average length of stay is the average number of days that the patients spend in hospital. 
It is calculated by dividing the total number of days stayed by all in-patients during a time period by the number of admissions or discharges.

ContainerSettings.Title: Average Treatment Cost by Age Group
ContainerSettings.Description: Average treatment cost is how much a patient cost for facilities. Here, it shows according to different age categories.

ContainerSettings.Title: Upcoming Appointments
ContainerSettings.Description: This table shows the details of the upcoming appointments that is doctor name, specialization, date and time, patient ID, and status.

ContainerSettings.Title: Patients Count by Specialization
ContainerSettings.Description: Specialization wise  inpatients and outpatients count.
